TY  - JOUR
AU  - Spencer, Barbara J.
AU  - Jones, Ronald W.
T1  - Vertical Foreclosure and International Trade Policy
PY  - 1991
Y1  - 1991/01/01
DO  - 10.2307/2298052
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 58
IS  - 1
SP  - 153
EP  - 170
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - International differences in the cost of production of a key intermediate product can mean that a domestic firm is dependent on supplies from a foreign vertically integrated firm. This paper considers the incentives for the foreign firm and foreign country to supply the domestic firm when the firms compete in a Cournot or Bertrand market for the final product. The vertical supply decision is significantly affected by domestic supply conditions for the input and a domestic tariff on final product imports. Optimal policy by the exporting country may require a tax on both exports, or a subsidy on both exports.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2298052
ER  - 



